properties.desc: Bins must be placed out by 6am on collection days and returned inside your property no later than the end of the day.Rubbish and recycling is collected on public holidays with the exception of Good Friday and Christmas Day.Collections from Thursday 25 December and Friday 26 December 2014 will be collected the DAY AFTER your usual collection.
properties.name: Thursday
properties.rec_ok: paper and cardboard; aluminium and steel cans; empty aerosol cans; all hard plastic containers; glass bottles and jars; milk and juice cartons; pizza boxes; aluminium foil and trays; rigid household plastic items like kitchen storage containers and plastic toys; steel pots and pans (note: no glass lids)
properties.rub_ok: general rubbish, nappies (wrapped), meat/bones; food scraps (also visit Home composting); non-recyclable plastics such as plastic bags, expanded polystyrene foam used in take-away coffee cups or packaging for electrical goods, plastic cling-film, plastic toys; CDs, DVDs, VCR tapes; broken ceramics, crockery, Pyrex, drinking glasses, mirrors or window glass (wrapped) and light globes; soft plastic that you can bend or scrunch (like plastic from a biscuit tray or cling wrap)
properties.rub_notok: hot liquid or ashes; oil; chemicals, paints and solvents (visit Chemical waste disposal); corrosive and flammable items (visit Chemical waste disposal); syringes (visit Needle and syringe disposal); car parts (visit Waste and Recycling Centre); soil, timber, bricks or other building materials (visit Waste and recycling centre); unwrapped vacuum dust; recyclable products (visit Household recycling)
properties.rec_notok: plastic bags; soft plastics; CDs, DVDs, VCR tapes; expanded polystyrene foam used in take-away coffee cups or packaging for household goods; batteries (visit Other recycling); ceramics; glass from broken glasses, windows or mirrors; waxed cardboard boxes; food scraps (visit Home composting); chemicals (visit Chemical waste disposal); nappies (visit Household garbage); light globes (visit Other recycling); syringes (visit Needle and syringe disposal); mobile phone and electronic and computer parts (visit Other recycling)
